cssforecast.reschedulecontact.col.label: Reschedule Contacts
cssforecast.helptext.line1: Contacts are counted only once against the first condition even if they satisfy multiple conditions.
cssforecast.helptext.line2: For example, assume you upload a single contact that satisfies two conditions – Condition 1 and Condition 2  If this contact satisfies both conditions, the Delivery Forecast counts this contact against the first condition only. Even though this contact satisfies the second condition also, the count against the second condition is shown as zero.

exclusion.helptext.heading: Exclusion Report Help Text
exclusion.helptext.description: Exclusion report shows the data for next 3 hours from the current time for all campaigns that are in the Executing state; also, for campaigns in the Time Suspended state that would get in to the executing state within prediction hours. See below for the column-wise descriptions:
exclusion.helptext.campaignName: This shows the campaigns that contain contacts in the Open state.
exclusion.helptext.opencontact: This shows the count of open contacts and the count of open contacts uploaded today, in separate columns.
exclusion.helptext.eligibleContact: This shows the count of contacts eligible for dialing and those eligible for dialing that are uploaded today, in separate columns.
exclusion.helptext.blockedContact: This shows the count of contacts blocked due to various criteria like DNC, NDNC, State Law, and CSS Conditions.
exclusion.helptext.Contacts: This shows the count of total contacts in the campaign. A break-up is also provided to indicate Fresh and Rescheduled contacts.
exclusion.helptext.ECT: This shows the estimated completion time for the campaign. This data is predicted for the whole campaign runtime and not for just the configured exclusion report hours.
exclusion.helptext.completionpercentage: The campaign completion percentage is calculated for the whole campaign runtime and not for just the configured exclusion report hours.

exclusion.helptext.openContactBOD: This shows the count of open contacts present in the campaign from beginning of the day. If new open contacts being added in the campaign those value will added in existing.This data is calculated for the whole campaign runtime and not for just the configured exclusion report hours.
